directions: Pre-heat the oven to 350 degrees. Butter a 9x13 baking dish.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt butter completely. Stir in sugar and continue cooking for 1 - 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Do not allow sugar mixture to boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in the Nutella until well combined.
Pour butter mixture into a stand mixer. Beat in cocoa powder, eggs, salt, baking powder, and vanilla extract.
Stir in the flour and baking melts until just combined.
Spread into prepared pan. Sprinkle the top with chopped hazelnuts, mini chocolate chips, and coarse sea salt.
Bake for about 30 - 35 minutes, until a tester comes out mostly clean. The edges should be set and the center should still look slightly moist, but not uncooked.
Cool completely on a wire rack. Use a knife to loosed the edges from the pan. Cut into squares and use a spatula to remove from pan.

title: greek style cucumber salad
directions: Peel the cucumbers, slice in half the long way and remove the seeds. Tip: use a grapefruit spoon to help with seeding the cucumbers. Slice the cucumber the long way again and slice into uniform pieces. If you want to make it into a salsa dice the cucumber smaller

Dice the red onion and red bell pepper. If want more color you can use a 1/4 cup each of red, yellow and orange bell pepper. Tip: if you do not like a strong onion flavor place the onions in cold water till you are ready to use them.
Slice the scallions into thin rounds
Mince the cilantro and red chili. Note: If you are not a fan of cilantro you can use parsley instead.
Zest the lemon and then roll the lemons on the counter and juice them.
Mix in a large non reative bowl all the ingreidents except for the feta cheese. Let sit for at least an hour for the falvors to meld together.
Right before serving crumble the feta into chucks and toss in to the salad.

title: grilled corn and bacon salad
directions: 1. Soak corn in water (10 minutes to an hour)
2. Grill corn (in husks) on the BBQ at medium.. Takes about 10-15 minutes. Turn while cooking
3. Take grilled corn and put into a brown paper bag and let it sit for a while (20 minutes at least or it is to hot to cut)
4. Once corn is manageable, cut off alls the corn into a large bowl. Allow corn to cool to room temperature.
5. Cook slabs of bacon (your choice in oven or in pan) until done (not overly crispy)
6. Dice onion and cook in reserved bacon greese til translucent (or carmalized if you prefer).
7. When onions are close to finished, open the can of chipotles and pour in the sauce from the can. (Unless you like extremely spicy food, avoid putting in actual pepper).
8. Mix bacon, onion mixture and corn together in a bowl.
9. add a little rice wine vineger and some salt & pepper
10. Serve when ready.

title: dutch oven bacon cheese pull aparts
directions: Cut each roll in half.
Pour butter into a 12-inch Dutch oven.
Roll cut rolls in butter until coated and arrange in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Cover with lid and let rise until double.
Bake at 350°F 20-25 minutes.
Dutch Oven Temperature Control using Briquets:
350°F in a 12-inch Dutch oven, oven top 16, oven bottom 8

title: fall vegetable slaw
directions: 1.	Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Peel the squash and dice into cubes about 3/4 of an inch thick. Toss in olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Put on a baking sheet and roast the squash until tender approximately 20 minutes and let cool completely.
2.	Add all the vegetables to a bowl and season with salt and pepper.
3.	In a small bowl, add the red wine vinegar, honey, Dijon mustard and herbs and whisk well to combine. Slowly add the olive oil and whisk to combine.
4.	Add the dressing to the vegetables and toss gently. Add the pumpkin seeds and toss. Serve immediately or place in a covered container.

title: molten chocolate lava cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350F
1. Melt chocolate on low flame in a double-boiler. When melted, take off flame and...
2. Stir in diced butter until it melts.
3. In another bowl, beat eggs and sugar, until it starts to whiten.
4. Stir melted chocolate into egg/sugar mix, then stir in flour.
5. Butter 4 individual ramekins and pour chocolate batter.
6. Bake for 10-12 minutes.

title: scallops with preserved lemons on the half shell
directions: 1. Heat oven to 250 degrees. Place scallop shells or oven-safe plates on a baking sheet and warm in oven.

2. In a saute pan, melt 2 tablespoons butter. Add shallot, garlic and all but two tablespoons of the parsley and saute for 2 minutes. Add preserved lemon juice or wine and simmer over medium heat for 1 minute. Set aside.
3. Sprinkle scallops with salt and pepper to taste. Place flour on a large plate and dredge scallops in it. Shake scallops to remove excess flour.

4. In a very large saute pan, heat remaining 2 tablespoons butter over high heat until it begins to sizzle. Add scallops in one layer, leaving at least a finger's width between them. Allow scallops to brown lightly on one side without moving them, then flip. Do not cook for more than 1 minutes on each side.

5. Once scallops are golden, add butter-shallot mixture to pan. Heat for a few seconds, then finish scallops with a sprinkling of preserved lemon rind and remaining parsley. Serve scallops immediately in heated shells or on plates.
